cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with object detection in thermal images using features borrowed from the visual RGB domain. This involves the use of image-to-image translation frameworks and a multi-modal architecture for object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multi-modal architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with object detection, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
